<section id="pagehead">
	<h1>Alvin Graylin of mInfo on China’s work &amp; management culture, and Asia-specific advertising techniques</h1>
	<img src="/images/go/AlvinGraylin.jpg">
</section>

<section id="content">
<p>Alvin is a technology entrepreneur and business leader with over 7 years of management experience in Greater China. Alvin co-founded mInfo, the leading Mobile Search Service in China providing natural language search services to users throughout China.</p>

<p>In this interview Alvin walks us through China’s business culture and shares his rich entrepreneurial experience in launching and advertising businesses in Asia.</p>

<h3><a href="/downloads/AlvinGraylin.mp3">download MP3</a></h3>

<h2>Highlights</h2>

<ul>
  <li>1:05: How Alvin’s company mInfo got to be partner of the Beijing Olympics.</li>
  <li>5:10: The general trend from B2B and B2Gov to a more human centered type of business.</li>
  <li>9:10: How a diverse cultural background can help bridge cultural differences in business between East and West. What are the relevant cultural differences and how deeper relationships matter in China.</li>
  <li>15:15: How to treat employees and create a company culture in the East.</li>
  <li>18:15: Trends in Chinese education and how it impacts company culture.</li>
  <li>21:13: How to train new hires and how it takes longer for Chinese employees to reach full independence. Where entrepreneurialism in China is really happening.</li>
  <li>25:10: Strategies for recruiting top talent in China.</li>
  <li>28:00: Managing western staff in China.</li>
  <li>30:00: How to release and market apps in China.</li>
  <li>33:15: Finding advertising channels to bring western products in front of a Chinese audience.</li>
  <li>35:25: What makes a truly successful company in China.</li>
  <li>38:50: What it takes for a western entrepreneur to do business in China.</li>
</ul>

